description: Britain is now launching a campaign to recruit more female forestry workers. 'Lumberjills' are being sought to ease a shortfall of around 100,000 jobs in the sector.

title: Western Australia bid to lure 30,000 British doctors, nurses, police and teachers Down Under
description: In a nod to the 'Ten Pound Poms' scheme introduced after the Second World War, government and industry officials will visit the UK to lure workers away to fill more than 31,000 vacancies.

title: MSU gunman's uncle says he was 'paranoid schizophrenic' who should have been locked up
description: Speaking in a telephone interview, Timothy McRae said that his nephew's mental woes worsened after his mother died from a stroke in 2020, where at which point he quit his warehouse job.
